<p>
    Esther turned 21 this past July 26 during our Somhlolo Festival of Praise.  She was part of the Administration team registering and welcoming children from various parts of the country. How many young ladies would give their 21 st birthday to be amongst kids aged 7-14 to celebrate and learn the depth of the divine heritage of our peoples.  This “Star” also a few weeks back volunteered to join Matrine a Lukhele, a saint of the age of 78, who serves to open the way for monthly Somhlolo festival of praise revivals held in each of the constituencies and chiefdomships throughout Eswatini.  Esther said these revivals are key to the revival that is sweeping our country and she wanted to learn how to enter and approach the leadership and those in authority so that when Mattine could no longer manage, then Esther could continue in her roles of opening the way for permission and cooperation in national and community leadership.  And yet this week we are approaching those leaders for permission to bury the Star, our Esther.
</p>
